--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
BEHAVIOR NOTES (implementation detail)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
- logs tail: prints all paginated history (limit 100 pages) or single page when
  --last N; then opens long-lived SSE on .../logs/stream; uses ureq because
  reqwest::blocking does not expose a streaming Read body suitable for SSE.
- attach: primary thread reads session events SSE; optional std::thread reads log
  SSE when --follow-logs (stdout may interleave; acceptable for v1).
- credentials show: sequential identity Get then AuthStatus with "---" separator.
- Server delete session: 204 on success, 404 if UUID valid but no row; cascades
  remove jobs/logs per initial_schema FKs.

